        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(reply): preserve sessions_send external routes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #88044.\n\n- preserve a target session's persisted external delivery context for internal `sessions_send` handoffs that enter through the internal `webchat` surface\n- carry persisted `deliveryContext.threadId` for inherited external routes so threaded transports stay on the stored thread\n- mark inherited external routes in `resolveEffectiveReplyRoute` so dispatch can route them without making `sessions_send` look like a Feishu/Telegram/etc. user turn\n- keep ordinary webchat turns on their live webchat route, and keep the stale-thread guard for non-inherited routes\n\n## Behavior\n\nBefore this change, an agent-to-agent `sessions_send` turn could arrive as internal `webchat` and then fail to deliver a reply back to the existing Feishu session, even when the target session still had a valid external `deliveryContext`.\n\nAfter this change, only `sessions_send` inter-session handoffs with a persisted deliverable external `deliveryContext` inherit that external route. If the persisted route has a `threadId`, dispatch passes it to `routeReply` only for that inherited route case. Normal Control UI/webchat turns continue to use their live webchat route, and ordinary routed replies still derive thread context from the active turn or thread-scoped session key.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node --require ./node_modules/tsx/dist/preflight.cjs --import ./node_modules/tsx/dist/loader.mjs .artifacts/proof/sessions-send-feishu-route-proof.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/effective-reply-route.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nFocused threaded regression on `b024b9902b`: the route resolver now preserves `deliveryContext.threadId=\"thread:om_123\"` for an inherited `sessions_send` external route, dispatch passes that same thread id to `routeReply`, and the existing stale-thread regression still proves ordinary/non-inherited routes do not resurrect a normalized stored thread id.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `sessions_send` replies can route through a target session's persisted external delivery context instead of being trapped as internal `webchat`; inherited external routes also preserve the persisted route thread when present.\n\nReal environment tested: original issue #88044 reports a real OpenClaw 2026.5.27 Feishu/Lark setup with 7 agents, `tools.agentToAgent.enabled=true`, and `tools.sessions.visibility=\"all\"`. The after-fix proof ran on patched branch `b024b9902b` using that same route shape: target session key `agent:B:feishu:B:direct:ou_xxx`, persisted `deliveryContext.channel=\"feishu\"`, incoming `InputProvenance.kind=\"inter_session\"`, `sourceTool=\"sessions_send\"`, and live provider/surface/originating channel all `webchat`. To avoid live credentials in the PR, the proof registered a Feishu outbound adapter and exercised the production effective-route resolver plus durable external-channel delivery boundary.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\nnode --require ./node_modules/tsx/dist/preflight.cjs --import ./node_modules/tsx/dist/loader.mjs .artifacts/proof/sessions-send-feishu-route-proof.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/effective-reply-route.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"inputProvenance\": {\n    \"kind\": \"inter_session\",\n    \"sourceTool\": \"sessions_send\",\n    \"sourceChannel\": \"webchat\"\n  },\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:B:feishu:B:direct:ou_xxx\",\n  \"persistedDeliveryContext\": {\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n    \"to\": \"user:ou_123\",\n    \"accountId\": \"work\"\n  },\n  \"liveTurnSurface\": {\n    \"Provider\": \"webchat\",\n    \"Surface\": \"webchat\",\n    \"OriginatingChannel\": \"webchat\",\n    \"OriginatingTo\": \"session:dashboard\"\n  },\n  \"effectiveRoute\": {\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n    \"to\": \"user:ou_123\",\n    \"accountId\": \"work\",\n    \"inheritedExternalRoute\": true\n  },\n  \"durableSendResult\": {\n    \"status\": \"sent\",\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n        \"messageId\": \"om_after_fix_proof_1\",\n        \"chatId\": \"user:ou_123\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"feishuSends\": [\n    {\n      \"adapter\": \"registered feishu outbound.sendText\",\n      \"kind\": \"text\",\n      \"to\": \"user:ou_123\",\n      \"accountId\": \"work\",\n      \"text\": \"QA-SESSIONS-SEND-FEISHU-PROOF\",\n      \"replyToId\": null,\n      \"threadId\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"observed\": \"PASS: sessions_send webchat handoff used persisted Feishu deliveryContext\"\n}\n```\n\nThreaded regression evidence after fix: `src/auto-reply/reply/effective-reply-route.test.ts` covers inherited `sessions_send` external route resolution with `deliveryContext.threadId=\"thread:om_123\"`, and `src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts` verifies `routeReply` receives that inherited thread id. The same dispatch test file still passes the stale-thread guard case where ordinary routed replies must not read `deliveryContext.threadId` from normalized session store state.\n\nObserved result after fix: the same route shape from #88044 now resolves the final reply route to `channel=\"feishu\"`, `to=\"user:ou_123\"`, `accountId=\"work\"`, marks it `inheritedExternalRoute=true`, and the external-channel delivery boundary calls the registered Feishu outbound adapter with the proof marker. The focused regression suite also passed 198 tests and confirms normal webchat turns still stay on `webchat` while inherited threaded routes preserve `threadId`.\n\nWhat was not tested: a fresh live Feishu tenant run against this patched branch was not rerun; the live Feishu evidence remains the original issue's redacted runtime logs, paired here with after-fix patched-branch external-channel delivery proof for the same persisted Feishu route shape and focused threaded route/dispatch regression coverage.\n",
